


----------------------------------------------------------
 CONFIGURATION
----------------------------------------------------------

- Before compiling with CUDA, set the path to CUDA Toolkit!
  File src/tnet.mk variable CUDA_TK_BASE

- In case you have 64bit gcc, with a different cross-compile 
  prefix than 'x86_64-linux-',please set CROSS_COMPILE
  in src/tnet.mk 

- Make sure you have gotoblas library


----------------------------------------------------------
 COMPILE
----------------------------------------------------------

- First we need to set dependencies:
cd src
make depend CUDA=true BITS64=true

- Then we can compile:
make #CPU implementation
make CUDA=true BITS64=true  #CPU+GPU implementation

- The binaries will be in src


- Makefile accepts following options:

   BITS64=true
   - enable 64 bit compilation (default is 32 bit)

   CUDA=true 
   - compilation with CUDA

   DOUBLEPRECISION=true 
   - using doubles instead of floats

   STK=true
   - build also STK dependent tools TMpeCu TMmiCu



----------------------------------------------------------
 DOCUMENTATION
----------------------------------------------------------

- Generate documentation by:

cd src
make doc

the html doxygen documentation is in directory doc/html
